Package: usedepartmenttheme
Title: Branded 'Quarto' HTML Themes for Departments and Institutes
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Jack", "Goodall", email = "jack.goodall@lshtm.ac.uk", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-0997-5528"))
Description: Installs a branded 'Quarto' HTML extension (format: dept-html)
    into your project with one function call. Four department themes are
    provided: lshtm(), lshtm_mrcg(), and lshtm_mrcu() for LSHTM and its MRC
    Gambia and MRC Uganda units (teal branding) and florey() for the Florey
    Institute. A generic custom() theme accepts any
    logo and base colour: lighter and paler tints are derived automatically
    from the single hex value, and the header text colour is chosen for
    readability based on the colour's luminance. Optional 'Quarto' settings
    such as a table of contents, code folding, and self-contained output are
    opt-in arguments rather than imposed defaults.
